(1305, 1, '2021-04-14 23:42:37', '2021-04-14 23:42:37', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What does EZ365 (or the Company) do with your personal information / user data? What are your obligations?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, share, and protect your personal information including user data. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand what we do. When required by law, we will notify you of any changes to this Privacy Policy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The types of user data we (or our vendors acting on our behalf) collect may include but may not be limited to the following:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Name (including Username)</li><li>Passwords</li><li>Addresses</li><li>Email address, Cryptocurrency address, Mailing Address</li><li>Financial Information  complete banking information including bank account and routing numbers and/or credit card numbers that you link to your account when you use the EZ Exchange PLATFORM.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Other personal information you choose to provide</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Additionally, EZ365 may prevent a person\'s identity from being connected with information. Although it will always remain confidential to the public, once we prevent a person\'s identity from being connected with information, it belongs to EZ365. Such user data may include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>User ID picture</li><li>Private blockchain data</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If we are unable able to identify a customer, we cannot complete transactions that require identification.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is the policy of EZ365 to request identification from all customers on the EZ365 PLATFORM. The information will not be used for marketing purposes if you do not wish to receive marketing messages from EZ365.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you are no longer a customer of EZ365, we will continue to share your information as described in this notice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We need to share certain customers\' user data to run EZ365s everyday business. When you use the EZ365 PLATFORM or other services available through EZ365s website, we automatically collect information from your devices. EZ365 also reserves the right and by purchasing EZX tokens, you have authorized EZ365 to verify users data or information, as required in accordance with any U.S. or foreign anti-money laundering or similar statutes, and to cooperate with regulatory or enforcement authorities if illegal activity is suspected by a EZ365 user.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We reserve the right to request certain information and user data from you in connection with your access and use of the EZ365 Platform to comply with applicable U.S. or foreign laws, or requests from a regulator. This includes the right to request you to unlock your ID picture or other similar identifying information for any reason while using the EZ365 Platform. As a user of the EZ365 Platform, you must comply with such requests. Failure to comply with such requests will result in your account being locked and access denied.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Any misuse of the EZ365 Platform for fraudulent or illegal activities will result in your account being locked and access denied.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Public Blockchain</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Information on any Public Blockchain belongs to EZ365 and is publicly visible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Information on the Public Blockchain, once recorded, cannot be removed. Such information is immutable and permanent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Private Blockchain</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Information on EZ365s Private Blockchain belongs to EZ365 and is NOT publicly visible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Information on the EZ365s Private Blockchain, once recorded, cannot be voluntarily removed, while it may expire at a given future date.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Cookies</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We use cookies  data captured by our server from your Internet browser and returned each time you subsequently access our server  to identify you and track your access to the EZ365 servers. You may elect to turn off all cookies through your browser settings and we will not be able to capture this data. If you turn cookies off, your experience with the EZ365 Platform may not be as efficient or user friendly as that of a user enabling cookies.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Protecting User Data</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We take reasonable steps to protect the security of the user data shared through the EZ365 Platform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our website and EZ365 Platform are scanned regularly for security and other potential vulnerabilities to make your use of the site as secure as possible. We do not, however, assume any responsibility for the data you submit to the EZ365 Platform or receive from EZ365. You agree to not hold us and our respective past, present and future employees, officers, directors, contractors, consultants, equity holders, suppliers, vendors, service providers, parent companies, subsidiaries, affiliates, agents, representatives, predecessors, successors and assigns liable for any loss or damage of any sort incurred as a result of any misappropriation, interception, modification, deletion, destruction or use of information provided through EZ365 Platform.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Sharing</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We will only share user information as described in this Privacy Policy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Third-Parties</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All non-public information that we receive regarding current or former users is held in the strictest confidence, and is not disclosed to others outside EZ365 except with your consent, as otherwise set forth herein or as required by law. We may disclose some or all of the information we collect, as described above, to certain non-affiliated third-parties such as attorneys, accountants, auditors and persons or entities who assist us in our business or who are assessing our compliance with industry standards, rules and regulations. We may also disclose information to regulators or other governmental entities as permitted or required by law. Your non-public personal information/user data is used only for our business purposes, and we do not sell client information to anyone. At your direction, we may share certain information with related or affiliated entities or third parties who assist us with providing our services including outsourced service providers located outside of the United States. These include but are not limited to, other firms such as accountants, lawyers, financial institutions and bill pay and electronic storage service providers, subject to the obligation of all such third parties not to use or disclose such information for any other purpose. Additionally, third-parties with whom EZ365 engages may collect personal data including financial data, and such use is governed by their privacy policy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Third-Party Payment Processor</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We use a third-party payment processor for all payments. EZ365 does not store credit card details and instead relies on its third-party payment processor for this. We use a third-party payment processor to process payments made to us. In connection with the processing of such payments, we do not retain any personally identifiable information or any financial information such as credit card numbers. Rather, all such information is provided directly to our third-party processor, whose use of your personal information is governed by their privacy policy, which may be viewed at <a href=\"https://www.ez365.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">www.ez365.com</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-04-14 23:42:37', '2021-04-14 23:42:37', '', 3, 'https://ez365.io/?p=1305', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
